snippet.textDisplay: I know I have a very low chance of Joey seeing this but he asked what he should do about the dry food so I’m going to answer lol. No don’t give her dry food at all. It’s more of a treat. Dry food can cause them to get overweight. When I got my cat she was 8 pounds and I fed her dry food for 4 1/2 years. She’s now 22 lbs and it started to kill her. I switched her to Honest Kitchen which helps for weight loss and it has all the nutrients a cat needs in it and only takes a few minutes to make. My cat Tiggy is doing so much better now. I give her a few dry food pieces every once in a while but she doesn’t really eat it. By the way stainless steel bowls are bad for cat’s and dogs teeth so I recommend ceramic bowls :)
